## 7. Hostel Allocation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[School Admin] --> B[POST /api/school-admin/hostels/allocate]
    B --> C{Request Type}
    C -->|Allocate| D[Validate room capacity]
    C -->|Deallocate| E[Remove allocation]

    D --> F{Room has space?}
    F -->|No| G[Return error: Room full]
    F -->|Yes| H[Check existing allocation]

    H --> I{Already allocated?}
    I -->|Yes| J[Free previous allocation]
    I -->|No| K[Skip]

    J --> L[CREATE hostel_allocation<br/>roomId, studentId]
    K --> L

    L --> M[Update room occupancy]
    M --> N[Allocation successful]

    E --> O[DELETE hostel_allocation]
    O --> P[Update room occupancy]
    P --> Q[Deallocate successful]

    style A fill:#8b5cf6
    style L fill:#d4edda
    style N fill:#c3e6cb
    style O fill:#ffd9b3
    style Q fill:#c3e6cb
```

**API Endpoints:**
- `GET /api/school-admin/hostels/allocate` - Get occupancy
- `POST /api/school-admin/hostels/allocate` - Allocate student
- `DELETE /api/school-admin/hostels/allocate?studentId=X` - Deallocate

**Database Tables:**
1. `hostel_buildings` - Buildings
2. `hostel_rooms` - Rooms with capacity
3. `hostel_allocations` - Student assignments
4. `users` - Student records

